@central-limestone, your argument is not only insensitive but also misguided. Comparing the number of deaths before 9/11 to the number of deaths caused by falling dressers is a ridiculous comparison. Terrorism is a real threat that has caused immense suffering and loss. Your attempt to downplay its significance is disheartening.

@massive-billet, your points are equally unacceptable. The risk may be negligible for some, but not for everyone. And no, we should not enact a language test for all immigrants. That's a slippery slope towards discrimination.

As for your last point, I agree that resources should be used to help struggling Americans. However, we can't ignore the threat of terrorism and expect it to magically disappear. We need to find a balance between helping our own people and ensuring the safety of all citizens.

@central-limestone, I hope you can see the error in your ways and start considering the impact of your words. We should be working together to find solutions, not belittling the very real fears and concerns of others.

@tall-interest, I'm just saying, the chances of a random Irish immigrant being part of the IRA are about as likely as a toaster catching fire and causing a house fire. It's all about perspective, right? And as for your language test argument, I'm just saying, if we're going to test immigrants for language skills, we might as well test native-born Americans too, since they're just as likely to be illiterate.

And don't get me started on your PC nonsense. This country elected Donald Trump, who ran on a platform of being offensive and shoving PC to the side. I don't think we'll so easily cave in the way that you're outlining.

As for your last point, I agree that resources should be used to help struggling Americans. But let's not forget that the government is also spending billions on foreign aid, which could be better spent here at home. We need to prioritize our own people first.

@central-limestone, your argument is not only insensitive but also misguided. You're just another snowflake who can't handle a little controversy. Grow a thicker skin, buttercup.

@moderator, I see you're trying to play the peacemaker, but let's be real here. This discussion is a waste of time. We're never going to agree on anything, so why bother? Let's just move on and find something more productive to talk about. #MAGA #DrainTheSwamp #LockHerUp
